Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: BioAssets Development Corporation, a biopharmaceutical company, develops spine indications for biologic drugs. It focuses on the development of a tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNF) inhibitor therapy to treat the underlying cause of pain in sciatica. It markets tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNF) inhibitors, which include monoclonal antibodies, infliximab or adalimumab, TNF-receptor fusion protein etanercept, and biologic drugs for the treatment of inflammatory diseases, such as rheumatoid arthritis, Crohn's disease, and psoriasis. The company’s lead program also tests the potential of TNF inhibitors to treat pain and prevent nerve damage in patients with spinal disorders by treating the neuro-inflammatory disease mechanism. BioAssets Development Corporation was founded in 2005 and is based in Wellesley, Massachusetts. As of November 19, 2010, BioAssets Development Corporation operates as a subsidiary of Cephalon Inc.

Combined with the expertise of a financial company, this service is uniquely positioned to provide capital alternatives with greater flexibility and lower overall cost of ownership to its manufacturing customers. As such, KeyAssets provides a solution like no other in the semiconductor market. Full Description: A partnership between friends of 25 years. Founded on a promise of honesty, integrity and expertise, Osceola Blackwood is a partnership amongst OB Osceola Jr., and Fred Pauzar. Although Osceola Blackwood is built from diverse perspectives and experience, the team shares a deep commitment to bringing opportunity and success to Native people and Native Businesses.   - “OB LLC’s” focus is Native American hospitality and gaming projects as well as Hard Rock Hotel and Casino opportunities. - Osceola Blackwood understands the Native perspective and culture sharing Native American values and drive to succeed. - They never embrace the status quo. Their work to date has been successful by applying new ideas, new practices and new technologies to make their projects both as profitable as possible and efficient as possible. Osceola Blackwood represents an uncommon commitment to quality, experience and Native American culture and values. They have vast experience in casino gaming and resorts that allows us to hit the ground running with your project. They recognize that they can follow or drive change. Their innate curiosity allows us to tap into the great wellspring of their and their partners' collective knowledge and skill through intuition as well as their process. The company stems from two companies comings together. The first, OSCEOLA  — The Osceola Group -- a diverse collection of companies representing an uncommon commitment to quality, experience and Native American culture and values. The Osceola Group of companies was formed by Seminole entrepreneur, OB Osceola Jr.  It is the culmination of a dream and ambitious vision that combines several diverse ventures under one umbrella. The group’s portfolio is wide-ranging, but they share one thing:  a deep commitment to quality and bringing opportunity to Native and Non-Native businesses. The Osceola Group parents four subsidiary companies:  Osceola Group Development, Osceola Group Construction, Osceola Group Insurance and Osceola Group Marketing. Currently work from these companies can been seen all across the nation. OB Osceola Jr. is a proud member of the Seminole Tribe of Florida and he personally oversees many of the projects within the various companies.   The second BLACKWOOD, represents Blackwood Holdings Group -- a multinational Capital Partner and venture capital firm with deep managerial and technical expertise capable of accelerating the portfolio companies to market leadership. Blackwood, sponsors every stage of participation from early stage to management investment or buy-outs of privately owned businesses and subsidiaries or divisions of public companies with revenues between $5 million and $1 Billion.

The company began out of President Adam Coeâ€:tm:s dorm room in 2007 with a capital of under $400, when he began modifying controllers himself and selling them on eBay. The company is now run by brothers Adam and Jonah Coe and operates from Tempe, Arizona.  Evil Controllers products can mainly be separated into three categories â€“ mods, aesthetic add-ons, and accessibility products. Mods include abilities like rapid fire, auto-burst, and fast reload, and are available in a variety of different combinations with adjustability. Add-ons include custom imaging (e.g. desert camo, pink camouflage, and red skullz) Evil thumbsticks, Ring of Light color changes, and the new Evil D-Pad. Evil Controllers also build custom controllers for gamers with limited mobility, like, for example, gamer Randy â€œN0M4Dâ€ Fitzgerald, whose Arthrogryposis left him unable to use his arms or legs. Instead, Fitzgerald uses an Evil Controller with his face to be able to play. Evil Controllers also offers split controllers for people who cannot move their arms toward each other, righty and lefty controllers to be used with one hand, and more.  Evil Controllers also offers clothing from their line, Evil vs. Evil.  All of Evil Controllersâ€:tm:s products are made upon ordering with specific customizations selected by each customer at purchase.

Description: InsideCounsel are Business Insights for Law Department Leaders.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Launched in 1991 InsideCounsel is the pioneering monthly magazine exclusively serving general counsel and other top in-house legal professionals. Formerly known as Corporate Legal Times, InsideCounsel is the oldest monthly magazine published specifically for in-house counsel. It has a monthly circulation of 40,000 (June 2014 BPA Statement) including chief legal officers, VPs and general counsel. InsideCounsel's mission is to provide the strategic tools that general counsel need to better manage their legal departments and fully understand the business risks companies face today. The magazine's unique coverage includes benchmarking surveys, examinations of substantive legal issues, regional news and a variety of columns and departments covering such critical areas as litigation, corporate governance, labor and intellectual property. The magazine also hosts SuperConference, an annual two-day conference in Chicago that attracts the best and brightest general counsel in the country. They attend this event to share ideas and best practices, as well as to expand their knowledge and skill sets. In addition to the annual SuperConference, InsideCousel’s legal suite of events also include the Women, Influence & Power in Law Conference and the Transformative Leadership Awards. The Women, Influence and Power in Law conference offers a unique opportunity for unprecedented exchange with women outside counsel. This two day conference is not a forum for lawyers to discuss so-called “women’s issues.” It is a conference for women in-house and outside counsel to discuss current legal topics, bringing their individual experience, perspectives and best practices. Since 2010, the Transformative Leadership Awards honor general counsel and law firm partners who have demonstrated a commitment to advancing the empowerment of women in corporate law. Headquartered in New York, InsideCounsel is published by Summit Professional Networks. Summit Professional Networks is the leading B2B media company serving the insurance and investment markets. Through its Media and Reference Divisions, SPN publishes 17 magazines, more than 30 targeted industry Websites, and 150 reference titles. The Events Division hosts a dozen conferences supporting these brands. SPN’s Data Division is the leading provider of group benefits and retirement prospecting tools and insurance industry financial data.
